																		New to the Circus Born Page.
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1956625&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183502" alt="DrChandra" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1956625)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;" >DrChandra</a></span> <span class="odate time_1504377408 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Sep 2017 18:36</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3583840">
									

<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Image source: Screenshot from He who gets slapped 1924, public domain according to <a href="https://archive.org/details/HeWhoGetsSlapped1924">https://archive.org/details/HeWhoGetsSlapped1924</a>. ProcyonLotor said it was okay to use.</span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">I don't know why there are 2 rating modules. If someone on the staff can fix that I would greatly appreciate it.</span> Thanks Levi for fixing that.</p>
<p>Credit to The Great Hippo's latest SCP about Tobin Hollis's magic book, which inspired this rewrite.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><strong>Edit:</strong> It's come to my attention that at least a small number of readers think the Clown in the image is Icky. It's not. It's just a random Clown (his name is Slappy, if you're curious), which is why the poster is advertising Clowns in general and only mentions Icky at the end. I'm not an artist, and thus couldn't draw Icky, so I just grabbed the creepiest public domain image of a Clown I could find. There's a detailed description of Icky in <a href="/former-assets">Former Assets</a>.</span></p>
<p><strong>Double Edit:</strong> I've now replaced the image with one actually of Icky (courtesy of <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zhange" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2938475); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2938475&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1540878144" alt="Zhange" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2938475)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zhange" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2938475); return false;">Zhange</a></span>) to avoid this issue entirely. It's occurred to me that The Exploring Series may eventually do a video on Herman Fuller, and when they do I don't want them to present an image of Slappy as Icky.</p>

							</div>

								
